        "steps": [
            "Ensure the remote-control snake is functional by inserting batteries into the egg remote and turning on the snake. Remove batteries after testing.",
            "Prepare the mono jack with a lead wire.",
            "Mark a spot on the bottom half of the egg remote, under the buttons, where the lead wires will exit.",
            "Open the egg remote by locating and removing the screw in the battery compartment.",
            "Carefully remove the circuit board from the front side of the remote, avoiding pulling on the wires.",
            "Tape down the black and red wires connecting the egg remote's shell to the circuit board.",
            "Drill a hole at the marked spot, large enough to accommodate the lead wire(s).",
            "Thread the lead wire(s) through the hole, ensuring the jack faces outward.",
            "Solder the mono jack wires to the silver dots on the circuit board corresponding to the desired buttons.",
            "Wrap electrical tape around any exposed wiring to prevent shorts.",
            "Test the connections by inserting batteries and plugging a switch into the mono jack(s).",
            "Reassemble the egg remote, carefully managing the lead wires within the shell and replace the screw."
